Given that your `versions` parameter is statically defined in the container, you could simply initialize your controller 
with this property and then use it in your method later on.

```php
return [
    'versions': ['1.0.1', '1.2.0', '2.0.0'],
    SummaryController::class => DI\autowire()
        ->constructorParameter('versions', DI\get('versions')),
];
```

```php
class SummaryController
{
    private array $versions;

    public function __construct(array $versions) {
        $this->versions = $versions;
    }
    
    public function summary(RequestInterface $request): ResponseInterface
    {
        // [...]
    }
}
```

If you're specifically looking for method parameter resolving, you can tweak your Slim app instantiation and add the
resolvers you need. You can use the [PHP-DI/Invoker](https://github.com/PHP-DI/Invoker#parameter-resolvers) library,
which is internally used by PHP-DI.
